Cell[TextData[{
 "The impedance corresponds to the reaction on the surface of the electrode: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["R", "1"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " is the resistance of the solution, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["R", "2"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " is the charge transfer resistance, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["C", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " is the double layer capacitance. The frequency in electrochemical \
impedance spectroscopy is normally calculated by the number of frequencies \
per decade. The Nyquist diagram plots the real versus the imaginary parts of \
the impedance."
}], "Text"],

